The paper proposes a distributed spectrum access algorithm for cognitive radio relay networks, which involves negotiation between primary and secondary users to satisfy their minimum rate requirements. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with information theory (cs.IT) and communication networks (cs.CR), which are also likely sub-categories. The use of decentralized algorithms and the focus on stability and optimality suggest that the paper may also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
